(1, 'UPSC (Union Public Service Commision)', 'upsc-union-public-service-commision', 'app/courses/2025/Feb/1740647495.jpg', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>What is UPSC and Why is It Important?</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>The Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) conducts India‚Äôs most prestigious Civil Services</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Examination (CSE) to recruit officers for:</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî IAS (Indian Administrative Service) ‚Äì Responsible for district administration, policy</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>implementation, and governance.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî IPS (Indian Police Service) ‚Äì Maintains law and order, counter-terrorism, crime prevention, and</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>public safety.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî IFS (Indian Foreign Service) ‚Äì Represents India in international diplomacy and manages</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>foreign relations.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî Other Central Government Services ‚Äì Includes Revenue, Railways, Audit, and more.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>ÔøΩ What Do Civil Servants Do?</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úÖ Policy-making &amp; Implementation ‚Äì Drafting and executing laws and government schemes.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úÖ Law &amp; Order Maintenance ‚Äì Handling law enforcement and judicial matters.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úÖ Economic &amp; Infrastructure Development ‚Äì Managing financial policies, taxation, and national</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>projects.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úÖ Foreign Diplomacy &amp; Trade Relations ‚Äì Representing India globally and strengthening</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>international relations.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úÖ Welfare &amp; Social Justice ‚Äì Ensuring education, health, and equality for all citizens.</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>ÔøΩ Why Choose Civil Services as a Career?</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî High Job Security</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî Power &amp; Influence</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî Challenging &amp; Prestigious Career</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>‚úî Diverse Opportunities Across Sectors</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>ÔøΩ Clearing UPSC = Becoming a Decision-Maker in India‚Äôs Government</b></span></p>', '[{\"key\":\"Duration\",\"value\":\"3 hours\"},{\"key\":\"Viewers\",\"value\":\"350\"},{\"key\":\"Lectures\",\"value\":\"15\"},{\"key\":\"Students\",\"value\":\"100\"},{\"key\":\"Certificate\",\"value\":\"Yes\"},{\"key\":\"Level\",\"value\":\"Beginner\"},{\"key\":\"Skill level\'s\",\"value\":\"All Levels\"}]', '[\"UPSC CSE\",\"UPSC Prelims\",\"UPSC Mains\",\"UPSC Interview\",\"UPSC Syllabus\"]', '[\"100% Free Coaching for UPSC Aspirants\",\"Expert Mentors & UPSC Toppers as Guides\",\"Best Study Material & Test Series\",\"Structured Learning for Beginners\"]', '[\"Daily 2.5-Hour Live Classes (Monday-Friday) + Doubt Sessions\",\"Prelims Crash Course + Daily MCQs & CSAT\",\"Mains Answer Writing Practice & Test Series\",\"Current Affairs Classes (Every Week)\",\"Optional Subject Coaching\",\"Mock Interviews & Personality Development\"]', '<ul><li>Prelims Mini-Tests Every Friday from March 2026</li><li>Current Affairs Classes Every Week</li><li>Full-Length Prelims Mock Tests in April-May 2026</li></ul>', '[\"Essay Writing Twice a Week (March-April 2026)\",\"Mains Full-Length Tests Increased in March-April 2026\",\"Mock Int