(2, 'SSC (Staff Selection Commision)', 'ssc-staff-selection-commision', 'app/courses/2025/Mar/1740831465.png', '<p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Course Overview</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\">Our UPSC (Union Public Service Commission) coaching program is designed to provide aspirants with the best resources, expert guidance, and a structured study plan to crack the Civil Services Examination (CSE). This comprehensive course covers the entire UPSC syllabus, focusing on conceptual clarity, analytical skills, and answer-writing techniques.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Modes of Learning ‚Äì Flexible &amp; Accessible</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\">We offer both online and offline coaching options to cater to students from different locations and backgrounds:</span></p><ul><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Classroom Coaching</b></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Live Online Classes</b></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Self-Paced Learning in your Nearby Location</b></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Essay Writing Practice</b></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Prelims Mock Tests</b></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Mains Answer Writing Sessions</b></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Ethics, Integrity &amp; Aptitude</b></span></li><li><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>personalized mentoring</b></span></li></ul><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\"><b>Description</b></span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\">The Union Public Service Commission (UPSC) exam is one of the most prestigious and challenging competitive exams in India. It is conducted annually to recruit officers for Indian Administrative Services (IAS), Indian Police Services (IPS), Indian Foreign Services (IFS), and other Central Government Services. To clear this exam, aspirants need structured guidance, expert mentorship, and a well-planned preparation strategy. Our UPSC coaching classes provide the perfect platform to help you achieve your dream of serving the nation.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\">We understand the challenges faced by aspirants while preparing for the UPSC Civil Services Examination (CSE). Our coaching program is designed to provide:</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\">Our team of highly experienced educators, retired civil servants, and UPSC toppers provide strategic guidance and personalized mentoring to each student.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\">Every aspirant has a different learning pace. We create personalized study plans to ensure effective time management and goal-based preparation. Additionally, regular doubt-clearing sessions help students resolve their queries instantly.</span></p><p><span style=\"font-size: 14.98px;\">Clearing Prelims and Mains is just part of the journey. Our UPSC Interview Guidance Program helps students develop the confidence, articulation skills, and presence of mind required for the final selection. Mock interviews with expert panels ensure that aspirants are well-prepared for the real UPSC interview.</span></p>', '[{\"key\":\"Duration\",\"value\":\"3 hours\"},{\"key\":\"Viewers\",\"value\":\"350\"},{\"key\":\"Lectures\",\"value\":\"15\"},{\"key\":\"Students\",\"value\":\"100\"},{\"key\":\"Certificate\",\"value\":\"Yes\"},{\"key\":\"Level\",\"value\":\"Beginner\"},{\"key\":\"Skill level\",\"value\":\"All Levels\"}]', '[\"SSC CGL\",\"SSC CHSL\",\"SSC MTS\",\"SSC JE\",\"SSC GD\",\"SSC Stenographer\",\"SSC Syllabus\"]', '[\"100% Free Coaching for SSC & HSSC Aspirants\",\"Expert Mentors & Toppers as Guides\",\"Best Study Material & Test Series\",\"Structured Learning for Beginners\"]', '[\"Daily 3-Hours Live Classes (Monday-Friday) + Daily Doubt Sessions\",\"SSC (CGL, CHSL, CPO, MTS) & HSSC (Group C & D) Crash Course\",\"Daily MCQs, PYQs & Subject-Wise Practice Tests\",\"Descriptive Paper (Tier-3) Writing Practice for SSC\",\"Current Affairs & Haryana GK Special Classes (Every Week)\",\"Advanced Maths, Reasoning & English Coaching\",\"Mock Interviews & Personality Development for SSC & HSSC\"]', '<p><span>Tier-1 CET, HSSC Group C/D Preparation:<br></span></p><ul><li>Weekly Mini Tests Every Friday (From March 2026)<br></li><li>Current Affairs &amp; Haryana GK Classes Every Week<br></li><li>Full-Length Mock Tests in April-May 2026<br></li></ul><br>Tier-2, Tier-3 &amp; HSSC Advanced Preparation:<br><ul><li>Advanced Subject-Specific Tests (March-April 2026)<br></li><li>Essay &amp; Letter Writing Practice (March-April 2026)<br></li><li>Full-Length Tier-2 &amp; SSC &amp; HSSC Written Exam Mock Tests (March-April 2026)<br></li><li>Mock Interviews &amp; Personality Development for SSC CGL, CHSL &amp; HSSC Officer-Level Posts</li></ul><p></p>', '[\"Strong Dedication & Commitment\"]', '[\"Strong Dedication & Commitment\",\"100% Free Coaching with Study Materials & Mentorship\"]', '<p><span>Staff Selection Commission (SSC) &amp; Haryana Staff Selection Commission (HSSC)<br><br>SSC and HSSC conduct exams to recruit candidates for Group B, C, and D government jobs in various central and state government departments.<br><br>Top Government Jobs Through SSC &amp; HSSC:<br><br>‚úî SSC CGL (Combined Graduate Level) ‚Äì Opportunity to become an officer in various central government ministries.<br>‚úî SSC CHSL (Combined Higher Secondary Level) ‚Äì Jobs like Data Entry Operator, Lower Division Clerk, etc.<br>‚úî SSC CPO (Central Police Organization) ‚Äì Opportunity to become a Sub-Inspector in Delhi Police, CISF, BSF, CRPF, etc.<br>‚úî HSSC Group C &amp; D ‚Äì Clerk, Patwari, Police Constable, Group D positions in Haryana government departments.<br>‚úî HSSC Haryana Police ‚Äì Opportunity to become a Sub-Inspector or Constable in Haryana Police.<br><br>What Do Government Employees Do?<br><br>‚úÖ Administrative Work ‚Äì Implementing government schemes and policies.<br>‚úÖ Maintaining Law &amp; Order ‚Äì Serving in police and paramilitary forces.<br>‚úÖ Finance &amp; Tax Management ‚Äì Handling revenue, audits, and accounts.<br>‚úÖ Banking &amp; Railway Sector ‚Äì Jobs in railways, banking, and insurance sectors.<br>‚úÖ Social Welfare &amp; Development ‚Äì Working in education, healthcare, and social welfare departments.<br><br>Why Choose SSC &amp; HSSC as a Career?<br><br>‚úî Job Security ‚Äì Permanent government job with a stable salary.<br>‚úî Attractive Salary &amp; Perks ‚Äì Competitive pay scale and allowances.<br>‚úî Career Growth &amp; Promotions ‚Äì Opportunity to reach senior positions.<br>‚úî Prestige &amp; Social Respect ‚Äì High recognition in society.<br>‚úî Pension &amp; Retirement Benefits ‚Äì Financial security after retirement.<br><br>üéØ Clear SSC/HSSC Exam = Secure a Government Job!</span></p>', '<p><span>1. Nationality Criteria:<br><br></span></p><ul><li>Only Indian citizens can apply for SSC &amp; HSSC exams.<br></li><li>For certain SSC posts, citizens of Nepal, Bhutan, and Tibetan refugees (as per government rules) may also be eligible.<br></li></ul><br>2. Educational Qualification:<br><br><ul><li>SSC Exams: Minimum 12th pass (for CHSL, MTS, Stenographer) or Graduation (for CGL, CPO) from a recognized university.<br></li><li>HSSC Exams: Qualification varies as per the post ‚Äì 10th, 12th, ITI, Diploma, or Graduation may be required.<br></li></ul><br><ul><li>No minimum percentage required.<br></li></ul><br>3. Age Limit &amp; Attempt Criteria:<br><br>Category &nbsp; &nbsp;SSC Age Limit &nbsp; &nbsp;HSSC Age Limit &nbsp; &nbsp;Number of Attempts<br>General &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 32 years &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 42 years &nbsp; &nbsp;No limit (Till age limit)<br>OBC &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 35 years &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 45 years &nbsp; &nbsp;No limit (Till age limit)<br>SC/ST &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 37 years &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 47 years &nbsp; &nbsp;No limit (Till age limit)<br>PwBD &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 42 years &nbsp; &nbsp;18 to 52 years &nbsp; &nbsp;As per category rules<br><br>4. Physical &amp; Medical Standards:<br><br><ul><li>Required for SSC CPO (Sub-Inspector in Delhi Police, CAPF) and HSSC Police (Constable, SI) posts.<br></li><li>Candidates must meet height, weight, vision, and fitness standards as per official guidelines.<br></li></ul><br>5. Reservation &amp; Relaxation Benefits:<br><br><ul><li>SC/ST &amp; OBC Candidates ‚Äì Age relaxation, fee exemption, and reserved vacancies.<br></li><li>EWS (Economically Weaker Section) Candidates ‚Äì 10% reservation in vacancies.<br></li><li>Ex-Servicemen &amp; PwBD Candidates ‚Äì Additional age relaxation and special reservations as per rules.<br></li></ul><br>üì¢ Check official SSC &amp; HSSC notifications for detailed eligibility criteria based on specific posts!<p></p>', '<p><span>Stage 1: Preliminary Exam (For SSC CGL, CPO &amp; HSSC Officer-Level Posts)<br><br>The Preliminary Examination is a screening test. Only candidates who clear the cut-off qualify for the next stage.<br><br>Prelims Exam Pattern (SSC CGL &amp; HSSC Group C Posts)<br><br>Paper &nbsp; &nbsp;Subject &nbsp; &nbsp;Marks &nbsp; &nbsp;Duration &nbsp; &nbsp;Negative Marking<br>Paper 1 &nbsp; &nbsp;General Intelligence &amp; Reasoning&nbsp; &nbsp; 25 &nbsp; &nbsp;Questions Yes (-0.50 per wrong answer)<br>Paper 2 &nbsp; &nbsp;General Awareness&nbsp; &nbsp; 25 Question &nbsp; &nbsp;Yes (-0.50 per wrong answer)<br>Paper 3 &nbsp; &nbsp;Quantitative Aptitude&nbsp; &nbsp; 25 Questions &amp; Yes (-0.50 per wrong answer)<br>Paper 4 &nbsp; &nbsp;English Language &amp; Comprehension&nbsp; &nbsp; 25 Questios &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;Yes (-0.50 per wrong answer)<br><br>‚úî Total Questions: 100 (Each question carries 2 marks)<br>‚úî Total Marks: 200<br>‚úî Cut-off varies yearly based on difficulty level and competition.<br><br>Syllabus Coverage:<br><br>‚úÖ General Intelligence &amp; Reasoning: Coding-Decoding, Blood Relations, Puzzles, Syllogism, etc.<br>&nbsp;<br>The rest of this will be found in your deshboard<br><br>‚úÖ General Awareness: History, Polity, Geography, Economy, Science, Current Affairs (India &amp; Haryana).<br><br>‚úÖ Quantitative Aptitude: Number System, Algebra, Geometry, Data Interpretation, Profit &amp; Loss, etc.<br><br>‚úÖ English Language &amp; Comprehension: Grammar, Vocabulary, Reading Comprehension, Sentence Correction.<br><br><br>Stage 2: Mains Exam (For SSC CGL, CPO &amp; HSSC Officer-Level Posts)<br><br>SSC CGL Mains Exam Pattern<br><br>Paper &nbsp; &nbsp; Subject &nbsp; &nbsp;Marks &nbsp; &nbsp;Duration<br>Paper 1 &nbsp; &nbsp;Quantitative Aptitude &nbsp; &nbsp;200 &nbsp; &nbsp;, 60 Minutes<br>Paper 2 &nbsp; &nbsp;English Language &amp; Comprehension &nbsp; &nbsp;200 &nbsp; &nbsp;, 2:30 Mins<br>Paper 3 &nbsp; &nbsp;Statistics (For Certain Posts) &nbsp; &nbsp;200 &nbsp; &nbsp;2 Hours<br>&nbsp;candidates applying for the Junior Statistical Officer (JSO) Post<br>Paper 4 &nbsp; &nbsp;General Studies (Finance &amp; Economics) &nbsp; &nbsp;200 Questions &amp; 2 Hours,<br>candidates applying for the Assistant Audit Officer (AAO) post.<br><br><br>candidates applying for the Assistant Audit Officer (AAO) post. <br><br>‚úî Total Marks for Mains: 400 (Only Paper 1 &amp; 2 for most posts)<br><br>HSSC Mains Exam Pattern (For Officer-Level Posts)<br><br>Paper &nbsp; &nbsp;Subject &nbsp; &nbsp;Marks &nbsp; &nbsp;Duration<br>Paper 1 &nbsp; &nbsp;General Studies &amp; Haryana GK &nbsp; &nbsp;100 &nbsp; &nbsp;90 Minutes<br>Paper 2 &nbsp; &nbsp;Subject-Specific (For Technical Posts) &nbsp; &nbsp;100 &nbsp; &nbsp;90 Minutes<br><br>‚úî Haryana GK Includes: History, Culture, Economy, Geography, and Current Affairs of Haryana.<br><br>‚∏ª<br><br>Stage 3: Skill Test/Descriptive Paper (For Certain SSC &amp; HSSC Posts)<br><br>‚úî SSC CHSL, Stenographer: Typing Test/Skill Test<br>‚úî SSC CGL Tier 3: Descriptive Paper (Essay &amp; Letter Writing) ‚Äì 100 Marks<br>‚úî HSSC Group C/D: May include a skill test or document verification<br><br>‚∏ª<br><br>Stage 4: Interview (For Certain SSC CGL &amp; HSSC Officer-Level Posts)<br><br>‚úî Conducted for selected high-level posts (Like HSSC Naib Tehsildar, SSC CGL AAO, etc.).<br>‚úî Marks: Varies based on the post (Usually 50-100 marks).<br>‚úî The panel assesses:<br>‚úÖ Decision-Making &amp; Problem-Solving<br>‚úÖ Current Affairs &amp; Administrative Knowledge<br>‚úÖ Leadership &amp; Communication Skills<br>‚úÖ Personality &amp; Ethical Integrity<br><br>‚∏ª<br><br>Final Merit Calculation:<br><br>‚úÖ SSC Prelims (Tier 1) ‚Üí Qualifying Only<br>‚úÖ Mains (Tier 2) ‚Üí Marks Counted for Merit<br>‚úÖ Descriptive Paper/Skill Test (If applicable) ‚Üí Qualifying<br>‚úÖ Interview (For Certain Posts) ‚Üí Merit-Based</span></p>', '<p><span><br>üìÖ Course Duration: 8 Months (30 April ‚Äì 31 December 2025)<br>üìö Class Days: Monday to Friday<br>üìù Test Days: Every Saturday<br>üì∞ Current Affairs: Weekly Current Affairs Classes<br><br>‚∏ª<br><br>üìå Subject-Wise Completion Timeline:<br><br>‚úÖ Mathematics: 10 Weeks (Basic to Mains Level)<br>‚úÖ Reasoning: 9 Weeks (Prelims + Mains Level)<br>‚úÖ English: 10 Weeks (Grammar, Vocabulary, Reading &amp; Writing)<br>‚úÖ General Awareness: 10 Weeks (Static GK + Current Affairs)<br>‚úÖ Computer Awareness: 2 Weeks (Basics Only)<br><br>üìñ First 5 Months: Concept Building + Topic-wise Tests<br>üéØ Next 3 Months: Full-Length Mock Tests + Advanced Practice<br><br><br>üìÖ Month-Wise Course Plan for SSC CGL 2026 &amp; HSSC<br><br>üìå Month 1: May 2025 (Basic Foundation)<br><br>üìä Mathematics: Number System, LCM &amp; HCF, Simplification, Percentage<br>üß† Reasoning: Analogy, Classification, Coding-Decoding, Blood Relation<br>üìñ English: Noun, Pronoun, Adjective, Synonyms-Antonyms<br>üåç General Awareness: Ancient &amp; Medieval History, Indian Geography<br>üì∞ Current Affairs: Weekly Update &amp; Quiz<br>üîπ Every Saturday: Topic-wise Test<br><br>üìå Month 2: June 2025 (Strengthening Fundamentals)<br><br>üìä Mathematics: Profit &amp; Loss, Simple &amp; Compound Interest, Ratio &amp; Proportion, Time &amp; Work<br>üß† Reasoning: Order &amp; Ranking, Venn Diagram, Mirror Image, Water Image<br>üìñ English: Tenses, Modals, Cloze Test, Reading Comprehension<br>üåç General Awareness: Modern History, Indian Polity, Basic Science<br>üì∞ Current Affairs: Weekly Update &amp; Quiz<br>üîπ Every Saturday: Topic-wise Test<br><br>üìå Month 3: July 2025 (Intermediate Level Topics)<br><br>üìä Mathematics: Algebra, Geometry, Mensuration<br>üß† Reasoning: Puzzle-Based Questions, Embedded Figures, Dice &amp; Cube<br>üìñ English: Active-Passive Voice, Narration, Error Detection<br>üåç General Awareness: Economy, Budget, Science (Physics + Chemistry), Current Affairs<br>üíª Computer: Basics of Computer, MS Office<br>üì∞ Current Affairs: Weekly Update &amp; Quiz<br>üîπ Every Saturday: Topic-wise Test<br><br>üìå Month 4: August 2025 (Advanced Concepts + Speed Building)<br><br>üìä Mathematics: Trigonometry, Data Interpretation (DI)<br>üß† Reasoning: Mixed Puzzles, High-Level Syllogism<br>üìñ English: Para Jumbles, Sentence Rearrangement, Advanced Cloze Test<br>üåç General Awareness: Government Schemes, Current Affairs (Last 8 Months)<br>üì∞ Current Affairs: Weekly Update &amp; Quiz<br>üîπ Every Saturday: Topic-wise Test (Prelims &amp; Mains Mixed)<br><br>üìå Month 5: September 2025 (Full-Length Practice for Prelims)<br><br>‚úÖ Daily Prelims Mock Tests (One Subject Per Day)<br>‚úÖ Revision of Weak Topics in Mathematics, English, Reasoning &amp; GK<br>‚úÖ Current Affairs Revision (Last 1 Year)<br>üì∞ Current Affairs: Weekly Update &amp; Quiz<br>üîπ Saturday: Full-Length Prelims Mock Tests<br><br>üìå Month 6: October 2025 (Mains Level Preparation Begins)<br><br>üìä Mathematics: Mains Level DI, Algebra, Trigonometry, Geometry Practice<br>üß† Reasoning: Input-Output, Syllogism, Logical Puzzles<br>üìñ English: Reading Comprehension, Precise Writing, Advanced Gramm